premise_source_doc_sentence: At the southeastern end of the archipelago , the eight main islands are -- in order from northwest to southeast : Niihau , Kauai , Oahu , Molokai , Lānai , Kahoolawe , Maui , and the Island of Hawaii .
At the southeastern end of the archipelago , the eight `` main islands '' are  (  from the northwest to southeast  )  Niihau , Kauai , Oahu , Molokai , Lānai , Kahoolawe , Maui , and Hawaii .

Hawaii is typically recognized by its eight main islands : Hawaiʻi , Maui , Kahoʻolawe , Lānaʻi , Molokaʻi , Oʻahu , Kauaʻi , and Niʻihau .
